# API

api> /issue

## Idempotency

The `/issue` endpoint is idempotent. If you send multiple requests with the same `iss` and `jti` values within a short window, the service will return the same `idx` and `uri` as the original successful response. This allows you to safely retry requests if you experience a network failure or timeout before receiving a response.

The `jti` claim acts as the idempotency key. You must use a new lowercase UUID `jti` for each new credential you issue. Do not reuse a `jti` across different credentials.

If you send a request with the same `iss` and `jti` but a different `statusExpiry`, the service will return a `400 BAD_REQUEST` error. You must generate a new `jti` for the new request.

If two requests with the same `iss` and `jti` arrive at exactly the same time, the service will return a `409 CONFLICT` error for the second request. Retry after a short delay.